CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 22, 1955, pg. 9, reads: "'We're After Five Million Too!' - Mrs. George L. West, fourth from the left, president of the Pittsburgh YWCA, tells Mrs. Laurance S. Rockefeller that the Pittsburgh Association has on a five million dollar drive also. Mrs. Rockefeller, chairman of the Centennial Observance of the YWCA of the United States, is heading a drive for a similar amount for the National YWCA.  Seated, left to right: Mrs. W. Sherman Skinner, Mrs. William M. Cuthbert, Mrs. Edward W. Macy, Mrs. West and Mrs. Rockefeller. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Mrs. W. Sherman Skinner, Mrs. William M. Cuthbert, Mrs. Edward W. Macy, Mrs. George L. West, and Mrs. Laurance S. Rockefeller, seated behind table with baby's breath and crystal candelabra at YWCA banquet
